'''ePages''' is an [[e-commerce]] solution that allows merchants to create and run [[Online shopping|online shops]] in the [[cloud computing|cloud]]. The number of shops based on ePages is currently 140,000 worldwide.
ePages software is regularly updated due to its Software-as-a-Service model.  An investor in the company is [[United Internet]], with a 25% stake.<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.united-internet.de/en/news-press/press-releases/press-releases-detail/news/united-internet-acquires-equity-interest-of-around-25-percent-in-epages.html | title= United Internet acquires equity interest of around 25 percent in ePages | publisher=United Internet | date= 19 February 2014}}</ref> ePages focuses upon distributing its products mainly through [[Internet hosting service|hosting providers]], such as [[1&1 Internet]], [[Strato AG]] or [[Webfusion|Webfusion’s]] brands [[Host Europe plc|Host Europe]] and [[123-reg]]. Additional sales partners include logistics, telecoms, and yellow pages companies. The company collaborates with 80+ technology partners including online marketplaces, payment and logistics companies, and ERP vendors. ePages is headquartered in [[Hamburg]], with additional offices in [[London]], [[Barcelona]], [[New York City]] and [[Jena]].

==History==
The name ePages was used for the first time for software in 1997 to market "Intershop ePages".<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.epages.com/en/company/ | title= ePages:  Online shop software for success in e-commerce | publisher=ePages | date= 19 February 2014}}</ref> In 2002, the product line then called Intershop 4 was taken over by ePages GmbH and renamed to ePages.<ref>{{cite web | accessdate= 28 April 2014 | url= http://www.channelpartner.de/index.cfm?pid=54&pk=631757 | title= Intershop-Gründer Beeck geht mit ePages erneut an den Start (Article in German) | publisher= ChannelPartner | date= 7 November 2007 | archive-url= https://archive.is/20140428210231/http://www.channelpartner.de/index.cfm?pid=54&pk=631757 | archive-date= 28 April 2014 | dead-url= yes }}</ref>

==Features==
Depending on the ePages product (Base, Flex, Enterprise, Multistore) and packages offered by hosting providers, merchants can sell up to an unlimited number of items. Users can offer their products and services in 15 languages and with all currencies. With ePages, merchants can use web marketing tools; e.g. newsletters, coupons or social media plug-ins for [[social commerce]].<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.epages.com/en/features/ | title= ePages features | publisher=ePages | date= }}</ref>
ePages has developed and optimised the shop content’s display on [[mobile device]]s <ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.internetworld.de/Nachrichten/Technik/Tools/SaaS-Shop-Systeme-Die-Wahl-der-Wolke-68509.html | title= Online shop software comparison (in German) | publisher= Internet World | date= 9 August 2012}}</ref> and added a filter search feature.<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://t3n.de/news/epages-615-onlineshop-system-469338/ | title= ePages 6.15: Onlineshop-System (in German) | publisher= t3n | date= 4 June 2013}}</ref> Further to this, major online market places such as [[eBay]] and [[Amazon.com|Amazon]],<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.existenzgruendungiminternet.de/strato-webshop-epages-im-test-erfahrungsbericht/  | title= Strato Webshop Epages im Test- Erfahrungsbericht (in German) | publisher= Existenzgründung im Internet | date= 8 January 2013}}</ref> search engines like [[Google]], payment providers such as [[PayPal]] and [[Enterprise resource planning| Enterprise resource planning systems]] such as SAP Business One<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.e-commerce-magazin.de/ecm/news/epages-mit-anbindung-sap-business-one-jetzt-demand | title= ePages mit Anbindung an SAP Business One jetzt on Demand (in German) | publisher= e-commerce-magazin | date= }}</ref> and Sage Office Line 24<ref>{{cite web | accessdate=28 April 2014 | url= http://www.itespresso.de/2014/04/22/sage-integriert-webshop-in-office-line-24/ | title= Sage integriert Webshop in Office Line 24 (in German) | publisher= IT espresso | date= 22 April 2014}}</ref> are integrated into the software.

In early 2017, ePages unveiled its latest generation shop software - ePages Now.  With the product, the company aims to facilitate accelerated multi-channel e-commerce success via rapid and easy deployment, shop functionality and features. The product is designed to address both modern shopper demands across sales channels, and sellers’ needs for efficiency and growth.

